{
  "texts": [
    "Lowry (Lowry et al. 2015) defined the \"place\" concept in their survey and discussed how VPR solutions can implicitly or explicitly account for changes in the environment's appearance.",
    "With the advent of deep learning-based image classification methods, recent surveys (Zhang et al. 2021; Masone and Caputo 2021) have focused on their application in VPR.",
    "VPR methods can be classified into two categories, depending on the camera sensor modalities used: partial-observable camera and fully-observable camera (Yin et al. 2022).",
    "The partial-observable camera includes pin-hole, fish-eye, and stereo cameras.",
    "Most VPR methods and datasets are developed based on this modality (Zaffar et al. 2021)."
  ]
}